WEBVTT

00:00:50.092 --> 00:00:53.136
- How about a ride, mister?
- Jennifer.

00:00:55.639 --> 00:00:58.183
Oh, man, are you a sight for sore eyes.

00:00:59.268 --> 00:01:00.727
Let me look at you.

00:01:00.811 --> 00:01:03.814
Marty, you're acting like
you haven't seen me in a week.

00:01:04.481 --> 00:01:05.732
I haven't.

00:01:05.816 --> 00:01:08.527
Are you okay? Is everything all right?

00:01:13.490 --> 00:01:14.700
Oh, yeah.

00:01:15.742 --> 00:01:17.536
Everything's great.

00:01:20.497 --> 00:01:22.833
(EXPLOSIVE CRASHING)

00:01:23.166 --> 00:01:24.585
(TIRES SCREECHING)

00:01:31.216 --> 00:01:34.886
Marty! You've got to come back with me!

00:01:36.638 --> 00:01:38.849
- Where?
- Back to the future.

00:01:43.145 --> 00:01:46.231
- Wait a minute. What are you doing, Doc?
- I need fuel.

00:01:48.442 --> 00:01:50.861
Go ahead. Quick! Get in the car.

00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:54.448
No, no, no. Look, Doc, I just got here, okay?

00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:56.908
Jennifer's here.
We're gonna take the new truck for a spin.

00:01:56.992 --> 00:02:00.078
Well, bring her along.
This concerns her, too.

00:02:00.162 --> 00:02:01.955
Wait a minute, Doc.
What are you talking about?

00:02:02.039 --> 00:02:03.790
What happens to us in the future?

00:02:03.874 --> 00:02:06.460
What, do we become assholes
or something?

00:02:06.543 --> 00:02:09.129
No, no, no.
You and Jennifer both turn out fine.

00:02:09.212 --> 00:02:12.424
It's your kids, Marty.
Something's gotta be done about your kids.

00:02:13.467 --> 00:02:15.177
(TIRES SCREECHING)

00:02:19.389 --> 00:02:22.809
Hey, Doc, we better back up.
We don't have enough road to get up to 88.

00:02:22.893 --> 00:02:27.314
Roads? Where we're going,
we don't need roads.

00:02:28.231 --> 00:02:29.775
Say, Marty!

00:02:29.858 --> 00:02:32.944
Marty! Marty, I wanted to show
you these new matchbooks

00:02:33.028 --> 00:02:35.155
for my auto detailing I had printed up.

00:02:39.034 --> 00:02:40.577
A flying DeLorean?

00:02:53.340 --> 00:02:55.717
What the hell is going on here?

00:04:25.515 --> 00:04:26.808
(BOTH SCREAMING)

00:04:26.892 --> 00:04:28.560
(HORN BLARING)

00:04:30.479 --> 00:04:32.689
- What the hell was that?
- Taxicab.

00:04:33.482 --> 00:04:35.442
What do you mean a "taxicab"?
I thought we were flying.

00:04:35.525 --> 00:04:36.526
Precisely.

00:04:36.902 --> 00:04:40.739
All right, Doc. What's going on, huh?
Where are we? When are we?

00:04:40.947 --> 00:04:44.409
We're descending
toward Hill Valley, California,

00:04:44.493 --> 00:04:49.623
at 4:29 p.m. on Wednesday,
October 21, 2015.

00:04:49.706 --> 00:04:51.374
2015?

00:04:52.793 --> 00:04:54.711
You mean we're in the future.

00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:58.465
Future. Marty, what do you mean?
How can we be in the future?

00:04:59.049 --> 00:05:00.383
Jennifer...

00:05:01.885 --> 00:05:04.179
I don't know how to tell you this,

00:05:04.930 --> 00:05:07.098
but you're in a time machine.

00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:11.853
- JENNIFER: And this is the year 2015?
- October 21, 2015.

00:05:12.229 --> 00:05:14.731
God, so, like, you weren't kidding.

00:05:14.815 --> 00:05:17.400
Marty, we can actually see our future.

00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:19.611
Doc, now, you said we were married, right?

00:05:19.694 --> 00:05:23.031
- (HESITATING) Yeah...
- Yeah? Was it a big wedding?

00:05:23.114 --> 00:05:25.075
Marty, we're gonna be able
to see our wedding.

00:05:25.158 --> 00:05:27.077
- Wow.
- I'm gonna be able to see my wedding dress.

00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:28.161
Wow.

00:05:28.245 --> 00:05:31.957
God, I wonder where we live.
I bet it's a big house with lots of kids.

00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:33.166
- How many kids...
- (DEVICE WHINING)

00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:36.044
- Doc! What the hell are you doing?
- Relax, Marty.

00:05:36.127 --> 00:05:38.755
It's just a sleep-inducing
alpha rhythm generator.

00:05:38.839 --> 00:05:39.840
She was asking too many questions,

00:05:39.923 --> 00:05:41.800
and no one should know
too much about their future.

00:05:42.008 --> 00:05:45.095
This way when she wakes up,
she'll think it was all a dream.

00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:48.014
- Then what did you bring her for?
- I had to do something.

00:05:48.098 --> 00:05:51.601
She saw the time machine. I couldn't
just leave her there with that information.

00:05:51.685 --> 00:05:53.895
Don't worry. She's not essential to my plan.

00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:56.565
Well, you're the doc, Doc.

00:05:56.648 --> 00:05:57.774
Here's our exit.

00:06:27.137 --> 00:06:29.264
First, you've gotta get out
and change clothes.

00:06:29.347 --> 00:06:31.558
Right now? It's pouring rain.

00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:36.521
Wait five more seconds.

00:06:44.195 --> 00:06:45.989
Right on the tick.

00:06:46.072 --> 00:06:49.451
Amazing. Absolutely amazing.

00:06:49.534 --> 00:06:53.288
Too bad the post office
isn't as efficient as the weather service.

00:07:00.837 --> 00:07:04.090
Excuse the disguise, Marty,
but I was afraid you wouldn't recognize me.

00:07:04.174 --> 00:07:07.010
I went to a rejuvenation clinic
and got an all-natural overhaul.

00:07:07.344 --> 00:07:10.972
They took out some wrinkles,
did a hair repair, changed the blood,

00:07:11.056 --> 00:07:13.975
added a good 30 or 40 years to my life.

00:07:14.059 --> 00:07:17.437
They also replaced my spleen and colon.
What do you think?

00:07:19.105 --> 00:07:21.358
You look great, Doc.

00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:25.362
The future.

00:07:26.404 --> 00:07:28.490
Unbelievable.

00:07:28.573 --> 00:07:31.242
- I gotta check this out, Doc.
- All in good time, Marty.

00:07:31.326 --> 00:07:32.452
We're on a tight schedule here.

00:07:32.535 --> 00:07:34.955
Tell me about my future.
I mean, I know I make it big.

00:07:35.038 --> 00:07:36.873
But what?
Do I become, like, a rich rock star?

00:07:36.957 --> 00:07:39.125
Please, Marty, no one should know too much
about their own destiny.

00:07:39.209 --> 00:07:40.627
Right. Right.

00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:44.589
- I am rich, though, right?
- Marty, please, take off your shirt.

00:07:45.674 --> 00:07:48.259
Put on the jacket and the shoes.

00:07:50.053 --> 00:07:51.930
Got a mission to accomplish.

00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:07.821
Ah-ha.

00:08:07.904 --> 00:08:09.280
Precisely on schedule.

00:08:14.828 --> 00:08:16.413
Power laces. All right.

00:08:34.472 --> 00:08:36.099
(WATCH ALARM BEEPING)

00:08:36.975 --> 00:08:38.560
This thing doesn't fit.

00:08:38.643 --> 00:08:40.603
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>Size-adjusting fit.</i>

00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:42.063
Pull out your pants pockets.

00:08:42.147 --> 00:08:44.941
All kids in the future
wear their pants inside out.

00:08:45.025 --> 00:08:46.443
Put on this cap.

00:08:46.526 --> 00:08:49.195
Perfect. You're the spitting image
of your future son.

00:08:49.279 --> 00:08:52.407
- What?
- Help me move Jennifer over here.

00:08:53.116 --> 00:08:55.577
- So what's the deal?
- Grab her feet.

00:08:55.660 --> 00:08:58.288
All right. Okay, now what?

00:08:58.997 --> 00:09:03.126
In exactly two minutes,
you go around the corner into the Cafe '80s.

00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:04.878
Cafe '80s?

00:09:04.961 --> 00:09:07.589
It's one of those nostalgia places,
but not done very well.

00:09:07.672 --> 00:09:10.300
Go in and order a Pepsi. Here's a 50.

00:09:10.383 --> 00:09:12.302
Then wait for a guy named Griff.

00:09:12.385 --> 00:09:14.137
- Right. Griff.
- Right.

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:17.182
Griff's going to ask you about tonight.
Are you in or out?

00:09:17.265 --> 00:09:18.725
Tell him you are out.

00:09:18.808 --> 00:09:21.227
Whatever he says, whatever happens,
say no, you're not interested.

00:09:21.311 --> 00:09:24.814
- Okay.
- Then leave, come back here and wait for me.

00:09:25.982 --> 00:09:29.569
Don't talk to anyone, don't touch anything,
don't do anything,

00:09:29.652 --> 00:09:33.323
don't interact with anyone
and try not to look at anything.

00:09:33.406 --> 00:09:36.117
I don't get it. I thought you said
this had something to do with my kids.

00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:38.328
Look what happens to your son.

00:09:39.829 --> 00:09:41.122
My son?

00:09:42.665 --> 00:09:44.918
God, he looks just like me.

00:09:45.001 --> 00:09:48.755
"Within two hours of his arrest,
Martin McFly Jr

00:09:48.838 --> 00:09:52.842
"was tried, convicted and sentenced
to 15 years in a state penitentiary."

00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.302
Within two hours?

00:09:54.385 --> 00:09:55.887
The justice system works swiftly
in the future

00:09:55.970 --> 00:09:58.139
now that they've abolished all lawyers.

00:09:58.223 --> 00:09:59.641
Oh, this is heavy.

00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:02.268
It gets worse. Next week, your daughter
attempts to break him out of jail,

00:10:02.352 --> 00:10:04.604
and she gets sent up for 20 years.

00:10:04.687 --> 00:10:06.773
My daughter. Wait a minute.
I have a daughter?

00:10:06.856 --> 00:10:09.567
You see?
This one event starts a chain reaction

00:10:09.651 --> 00:10:11.444
that completely destroys your entire family.

00:10:11.528 --> 00:10:12.779
(EXCLAIMS)

00:10:12.862 --> 00:10:15.949
Hey, Doc, this date...
This is tomorrow's newspaper.

00:10:16.032 --> 00:10:19.410
Precisely, I already went further ahead
into time to see what else happens.

00:10:19.494 --> 00:10:22.122
I backtracked everything to this one event.
That's why we're here today,

00:10:22.205 --> 00:10:23.665
to prevent this incident
from ever happening.

00:10:23.748 --> 00:10:24.999
(BEEPING)

00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:26.918
Damn! I'm late!

00:10:27.001 --> 00:10:29.796
- Wait a minute. Where you going now?
- To intercept the real Marty Jr.

00:10:29.879 --> 00:10:32.298
You're taking his place.
Around the corner at the Cafe '80s.

00:10:32.382 --> 00:10:34.467
Guy named Griff. Just say no!

00:10:35.093 --> 00:10:37.679
Hey, what about Jennifer?
We're not just gonna leave her here.

00:10:37.762 --> 00:10:40.723
Don't worry, she'll be safe.
It'll just be for a few minutes.

00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:43.017
And, Marty, be careful around
that Griff character.

00:10:43.101 --> 00:10:46.563
He's got a few short circuits
in his bionic implants.

00:10:49.983 --> 00:10:51.526
MARTY: The future.

00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:44.621
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>Welcome to Texaco.</i>

00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:48.875
<i>You can trust your car
to the system with the star.</i>

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:52.587
<i>Checking oil. Checking landing gear.</i>

00:11:52.670 --> 00:11:54.797
<i>(JAWS</i> THEME PLAYING)

00:11:59.344 --> 00:12:00.762
(SCREAMING)

00:12:08.228 --> 00:12:09.562
The shark still looks fake.

00:12:09.646 --> 00:12:11.940
- (MUSIC BLARING)
<i>- Hi, friends. Goldie Wilson III</i>

00:12:12.023 --> 00:12:13.816
<i>for Wilson Hover Conversion Systems.</i>

00:12:14.192 --> 00:12:17.445
<i>You know, when my grandpa
was mayor of Hill Valley,</i>

00:12:17.528 --> 00:12:19.906
<i>he had to worry about traffic problems.</i>

00:12:19.989 --> 00:12:22.742
<i>But now, you don't have
to worry about traffic.</i>

00:12:22.825 --> 00:12:25.662
<i>I'll hover-convert your old road car</i>

00:12:25.745 --> 00:12:32.168
<i>into a skyway flyer for only $39,999.95.</i>

00:12:32.293 --> 00:12:35.588
<i>So come on down and see me,
Goldie Wilson III,</i>

00:12:35.672 --> 00:12:38.841
<i>at any one of our 29 convenient locations.</i>

00:12:38.925 --> 00:12:41.010
<i>Remember, keep 'em flying.</i>

00:12:45.515 --> 00:12:47.642
('80S POP MUSIC PLAYING)

00:12:56.985 --> 00:12:58.945
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

00:13:03.533 --> 00:13:06.661
<i>It's got a hot salsa, avocados,</i>

00:13:06.744 --> 00:13:11.708
<i>cilantro mixed with your choice
of beans, chicken, beef or pork.</i>

00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:14.252
Waiter. Waiter.

00:13:16.212 --> 00:13:17.630
(WHIRRING)

00:13:17.714 --> 00:13:19.340
<i>Welcome to the Cafe '80s,</i>

00:13:19.424 --> 00:13:23.136
<i>where it's always morning in America,
even in the afternoon.</i>

00:13:23.219 --> 00:13:24.721
(LAUGHING)

00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:27.348
<i>Our special today is mesquite-grilled sushi.</i>

00:13:27.432 --> 00:13:29.767
<i>- You must have the hostage special!
- Cajun style.</i>

00:13:29.851 --> 00:13:31.728
- (DISTORTED)
<i>- You must have the hostage special!</i>

00:13:31.811 --> 00:13:34.814
<i>You must have the hostage special!</i>

00:13:34.897 --> 00:13:38.067
Hey, hey, hey, guys! Hey, hey, guys!

00:13:38.151 --> 00:13:39.736
All I want is a Pepsi.

00:13:45.199 --> 00:13:46.826
Hey, McFly!

00:13:47.994 --> 00:13:50.246
Yeah. I've seen you around.

00:13:50.997 --> 00:13:53.249
You're Marty McFly's kid, aren't you?

00:13:54.334 --> 00:13:57.045
- Biff?
- You're Marty Jr.

00:13:57.879 --> 00:13:59.005
Tough break, kid.

00:13:59.088 --> 00:14:02.050
Must be rough being named after
a complete butthead.

00:14:02.133 --> 00:14:03.509
What's that supposed to mean?

00:14:03.593 --> 00:14:06.554
- Hello? Hello? Anybody home?
- Hey. Hey.

00:14:06.637 --> 00:14:08.348
Think, McFly, think!

00:14:08.431 --> 00:14:11.267
Your old man? Mr. Loser?

00:14:11.768 --> 00:14:13.770
- What?
- That's right.

00:14:14.354 --> 00:14:16.731
Loser with a capital "L."

00:14:17.440 --> 00:14:19.817
Look, I happen to know
George McFly is no longer a loser.

00:14:19.901 --> 00:14:23.279
No, I'm not talking about George McFly.
I'm talking about his kid.

00:14:23.446 --> 00:14:27.033
Your old man, Marty McFly Sr.,

00:14:27.533 --> 00:14:31.954
the man who took his life
and flushed it completely down the toilet.

00:14:33.289 --> 00:14:34.540
I did?

00:14:35.625 --> 00:14:37.794
(STUTTERING) I mean... I mean, he did?

00:14:38.669 --> 00:14:39.879
Hey, Gramps,

00:14:39.962 --> 00:14:43.049
I told you two coats of wax on my car,
not just one!

00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:46.594
Hey, hey, I just put the second coat on
last week.

00:14:46.677 --> 00:14:49.555
- Yeah? With your eyes closed?
- Are you two related?

00:14:49.639 --> 00:14:53.142
Hello? Hello? Anybody home?

00:14:53.226 --> 00:14:55.978
What do you think,
Griff just calls me "Grandpa" for his health?

00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:57.980
- He's Griff?
- Gramps!

00:14:58.731 --> 00:15:00.900
What the hell am I paying you for?

00:15:00.983 --> 00:15:03.986
Hey, kid, say hello to your grandma for me.

00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:07.532
- Get out here, Gramps.
- OLDEST BIFF: Hey, take it easy!

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:12.036
And, McFly, don't go anywhere! You're next!

00:15:14.414 --> 00:15:16.666
BOY: This is a video game.

00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:18.292
(MUSIC PLAYING ON VIDEO GAME)

00:15:18.376 --> 00:15:20.086
I got it working.

00:15:20.169 --> 00:15:22.505
My dad taught me about these.

00:15:22.797 --> 00:15:24.674
MARTY: It is <i>Wild Gunman.</i>

00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:26.300
How do you play this thing?

00:15:26.384 --> 00:15:28.177
I'll show you, kid.

00:15:29.137 --> 00:15:31.055
I'm a crack shot at this.

00:15:36.936 --> 00:15:38.438
BOY: You mean you have to use your hands?

00:15:38.521 --> 00:15:40.690
That's like a baby's toy.

00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:44.527
Baby's toy?

00:15:52.785 --> 00:15:54.120
Pepsi Perfect.

00:15:54.203 --> 00:15:56.038
- Damn!
- Pepsi.

00:15:58.207 --> 00:15:59.792
GRIFF: Hey, McFly!

00:16:01.210 --> 00:16:03.296
I thought I told you to stay in here!

00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:06.757
Griff. Guys, how's it going?

00:16:07.758 --> 00:16:09.427
- McFly!
- Yeah?

00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:11.846
- McFly!
- What?

00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:13.431
Your shoe's unvelked.

00:16:14.056 --> 00:16:15.391
(GRIFF LAUGHING)

00:16:16.267 --> 00:16:18.311
(LAUGHING SHEEPISHLY)

00:16:18.603 --> 00:16:24.233
So, McFly, have you made a decision
about tonight's opportunity?

00:16:24.317 --> 00:16:26.277
Yeah, Griff. You know,
I was thinking about it. I'm not sure,

00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:30.656
because I just think, you know,
it might be a little bit dangerous, so...

00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:32.033
What's wrong, McFly?

00:16:32.116 --> 00:16:33.159
(WHIMPERING)

00:16:33.242 --> 00:16:34.994
