00:24:02.024 --> 00:24:05.069
Yes! Yes, of course!

00:24:06.236 --> 00:24:10.449
Because this Hoverboard incident
has now occurred, Griff now goes to jail.

00:24:10.532 --> 00:24:12.034
Therefore, your son won't go
with him tonight,

00:24:12.117 --> 00:24:13.994
and that robbery will never take place.

00:24:14.078 --> 00:24:19.416
Thus, history, future history,
has now been altered, and this is the proof!

00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:21.835
Marty, we've succeeded,
not exactly as I planned, but no matter.

00:24:21.919 --> 00:24:24.046
Let's go get Jennifer and go home!

00:24:26.465 --> 00:24:28.384
- Hi, Einie. Hi, buddy.
- (WHIMPERING)

00:24:30.010 --> 00:24:32.346
- What's this?
- It's a souvenir.

00:24:32.429 --> 00:24:34.723
"50 years of sports statistics."

00:24:34.807 --> 00:24:37.059
Hardly recreational reading material, Marty.

00:24:37.142 --> 00:24:40.437
Well, hey, Doc, what's the harm
in bringing back a little info on the future?

00:24:40.521 --> 00:24:42.564
You know,
maybe we could place a couple bets.

00:24:42.648 --> 00:24:46.652
Marty, I didn't invent the time machine
for financial gain!

00:24:46.735 --> 00:24:49.446
The intent here is to gain
a clearer perception of humanity.

00:24:49.530 --> 00:24:50.948
Where we've been, where we're going,

00:24:51.031 --> 00:24:54.201
the pitfalls and the possibilities,
the perils and the promise.

00:24:54.284 --> 00:24:57.579
Perhaps even an answer
to that universal question, "Why?"

00:24:57.663 --> 00:24:59.832
Hey, Doc, I'm all for that.

00:24:59.915 --> 00:25:02.418
What's wrong with making
a few bucks on the side?

00:25:02.501 --> 00:25:06.005
I am going to put this in the trash.

00:25:06.088 --> 00:25:07.840
(CHATTERING ON POLICE RADIO)

00:25:07.923 --> 00:25:09.299
Great Scott!

00:25:12.761 --> 00:25:18.517
McFly, Jennifer Jane Parker,
3793 Oakhurst Street, Hilldale, age 47.

00:25:18.726 --> 00:25:21.311
Forty-seven? That's a hell of a good face-lift.

00:25:21.729 --> 00:25:24.940
- What the hell are they doing, Doc?
- They used her thumbprint to assess her ID.

00:25:25.024 --> 00:25:26.650
Since her thumbprint
never changes over the years,

00:25:26.734 --> 00:25:28.861
they simply assume
she's the Jennifer of the future.

00:25:28.944 --> 00:25:30.154
Well, we gotta stop them.

00:25:30.237 --> 00:25:33.240
What are we gonna say? That we're
time travelers? They'd have us committed.

00:25:33.323 --> 00:25:35.701
She's clean. That means we take her home.

00:25:35.784 --> 00:25:39.079
Home? To Hilldale?
It'll be dark by the time we get out there.

00:25:39.163 --> 00:25:42.541
That's it. They're taking her home
to your future home!

00:25:42.624 --> 00:25:45.919
We'll arrive shortly thereafter,
get her out of there and go back to 1985.

00:25:46.003 --> 00:25:48.881
You mean I'm gonna see where I live?
I'm gonna see myself as an old man?

00:25:48.964 --> 00:25:52.092
No, no, no, Marty. That could result in...
(GASPS) Great Scott!

00:25:52.551 --> 00:25:55.304
Jennifer could conceivably encounter
her future self!

00:25:55.387 --> 00:25:58.432
The consequences of that
could be disastrous!

00:25:58.515 --> 00:26:01.268
- Doc, what do you mean?
- I foresee two possibilities.

00:26:01.351 --> 00:26:03.854
One, coming face to face
with herself 30 years older

00:26:03.937 --> 00:26:06.065
would put her into shock,
and she'd simply pass out,

00:26:06.148 --> 00:26:08.817
or two, the encounter could create
a time paradox,

00:26:08.901 --> 00:26:11.570
the results of which could cause
a chain reaction that would unravel

00:26:11.653 --> 00:26:15.657
the very fabric of the space-time continuum
and destroy the entire universe!

00:26:15.741 --> 00:26:17.451
Granted, that's a worst-case scenario.

00:26:17.534 --> 00:26:19.161
The destruction might, in fact,
be very localized,

00:26:19.244 --> 00:26:21.497
limited to merely our own galaxy.

00:26:22.372 --> 00:26:24.249
Well, that's a relief.

00:26:28.170 --> 00:26:31.840
Let's go. I sure hope we find Jennifer
before she finds herself.

00:26:33.509 --> 00:26:36.637
The skyway's jammed.
It's gonna take us forever to get there.

00:26:36.720 --> 00:26:38.222
And this stays here.

00:26:38.305 --> 00:26:40.307
I didn't invent the time machine
to win at gambling.

00:26:40.390 --> 00:26:42.768
I invented a time machine
to travel through time!

00:26:42.851 --> 00:26:44.853
I know. I know. I know, Doc.

00:26:54.071 --> 00:26:58.534
So, Doc Brown invented a time machine.

00:27:24.893 --> 00:27:26.395
Hilldale.

00:27:27.396 --> 00:27:31.233
Nothing but a breeding ground
for tranks, lobos and zipheads.

00:27:31.316 --> 00:27:33.193
Yeah, they ought to tear
this whole place down.

00:27:34.570 --> 00:27:35.571
(BEEPS)

00:27:35.654 --> 00:27:36.780
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>Welcome home, Jennifer.</i>

00:27:36.864 --> 00:27:37.990
Whoa!

00:27:38.657 --> 00:27:40.033
- You all right?
- Yeah.

00:27:40.117 --> 00:27:42.870
You got a little tranked,
but I think you can walk.

00:27:42.953 --> 00:27:46.498
Ma'am, you should reprogram.
It's dangerous to enter without lights on.

00:27:46.582 --> 00:27:48.584
- JENNIFER: Lights on?
- Yes. Now, look.

00:27:49.793 --> 00:27:54.089
Just take it easy and you'll be fine.
And be careful in the future.

00:27:55.090 --> 00:27:56.592
The future?

00:27:57.885 --> 00:27:59.928
Have a nice day, Mrs. McFly.

00:28:02.681 --> 00:28:06.059
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>Broadcasting beautiful views 24 hours a day,</i>

00:28:06.143 --> 00:28:08.437
<i>you're tuned to the Scenery Channel.</i>

