00:34:44.124 --> 00:34:47.419
<i>- The Jits will never find out.</i>
- Oh, God.

00:34:47.502 --> 00:34:52.090
<i>Come on.
Stick your card in the slot, and I'll handle it.</i>

00:34:52.757 --> 00:34:56.845
<i>Unless you want everyone in the division
to think you're chicken.</i>

00:35:01.391 --> 00:35:04.644
Nobody calls me chicken, Needles.

00:35:04.728 --> 00:35:06.771
- Nobody!
- NEEDLES: <i>All right.</i>

00:35:07.814 --> 00:35:09.024
<i>Prove it.</i>

00:35:13.570 --> 00:35:15.071
All right.

00:35:15.572 --> 00:35:17.365
All right, Needles.

00:35:19.075 --> 00:35:20.410
(SCOFFS)

00:35:20.744 --> 00:35:24.039
Here's my card. Scan it. I'm in.

00:35:24.581 --> 00:35:27.542
<i>Thanks, McFly.
I'll see you at the plant tomorrow.</i>

00:35:29.377 --> 00:35:30.545
(AUTOMATED VOICE READING)

00:35:30.629 --> 00:35:31.963
Chicken.

00:35:33.715 --> 00:35:35.091
<i>McFly!</i>

00:35:35.884 --> 00:35:38.470
(GREETING IN JAPANESE)

00:35:38.553 --> 00:35:43.058
<i>McFly, I was monitoring
that scan you just interfaced.</i>

00:35:43.141 --> 00:35:44.809
<i>You are terminated!</i>

00:35:44.893 --> 00:35:48.396
Terminated. No! No! It wasn't my fault, sir.
It was Needles.

00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:50.649
- Needles was behind the whole thing.
<i>- And you cooperated.</i>

00:35:50.732 --> 00:35:52.859
- No, I didn't. It was a sting operation.
<i>- It was illegal.</i>

00:35:52.942 --> 00:35:55.987
- I was setting him up.
<i>- And you knew. McFly, read my fax!</i>

00:35:56.071 --> 00:36:00.200
No! Please, no. I cannot be fired. I'm fired.

00:36:00.283 --> 00:36:02.118
(EXCLAIMS IN DISAPPOINTMENT)

00:36:02.243 --> 00:36:04.537
(WHIRRING)

00:36:11.419 --> 00:36:13.922
Oh, this is heavy.

00:36:14.756 --> 00:36:17.342
What am I going to tell Jennifer?

00:36:17.425 --> 00:36:19.094
Jennifer. Jennifer.

00:36:19.427 --> 00:36:21.763
Oh, Doc, am I glad to see you.

00:36:22.263 --> 00:36:25.350
Go out the front door. I'll meet you there.

00:36:25.433 --> 00:36:27.936
But it doesn't open. There's no doorknob.

00:36:28.019 --> 00:36:30.230
Press your thumb to the plate.

00:36:30.313 --> 00:36:32.190
What plate?

00:36:45.120 --> 00:36:46.204
(DOOR OPENS)

00:36:46.287 --> 00:36:48.331
Marty, what does this fax mean?

00:36:48.415 --> 00:36:51.543
Oh, Mom, it's a joke, an office joke.
Kind of a joke fax.

00:36:51.626 --> 00:36:52.836
OLDEST LORRAINE:
Marty, I heard you yelling.

00:36:52.919 --> 00:36:54.754
Mom, Mom, Mom, calm down.

00:36:54.838 --> 00:36:57.132
I wasn't yelling.
Needles and I were just kind of joking.

00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:58.299
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>Welcome home, Jennifer.</i>

00:36:58.383 --> 00:36:59.426
OLDEST LORRAINE:
Marty, have you lost your job?

00:36:59.509 --> 00:37:02.011
Lost my job, Mom? Get out of town.
Look, you know...

00:37:05.473 --> 00:37:06.766
(BOTH GASPING)

00:37:06.850 --> 00:37:08.893
- I'm young!
- I'm old!

00:37:18.153 --> 00:37:19.738
Marty! Marty!

00:37:19.821 --> 00:37:21.865
Marty, come quick! Quick!

00:37:27.954 --> 00:37:29.497
(GRUNTING)

00:37:29.873 --> 00:37:31.166
(GROANING)

00:37:37.505 --> 00:37:41.468
She encountered her older self
and went into shock, just as I predicted.

00:37:41.551 --> 00:37:43.011
She'll be fine.

00:37:43.094 --> 00:37:45.263
Let's get her back to 1985,

00:37:45.346 --> 00:37:48.141
and then I'm gonna destroy
the time machine.

00:37:48.224 --> 00:37:49.309
Destroy it?

00:37:49.392 --> 00:37:52.812
What about that stuff about humanity,
where we're going and why?

00:37:52.896 --> 00:37:55.440
The risks are just too great,
as this incident proves.

00:37:55.523 --> 00:37:58.151
And I was behaving responsibly.
You can imagine the danger

00:37:58.234 --> 00:38:00.278
if the time machine were
to fall into the wrong hands.

00:38:00.904 --> 00:38:02.530
(GROANING)

00:38:03.531 --> 00:38:08.411
My only regret is that I'll never get a chance
to visit my favorite historical era,

00:38:08.620 --> 00:38:10.038
the Old West.

00:38:10.413 --> 00:38:14.167
But time traveling is just too dangerous.

00:38:14.250 --> 00:38:20.173
Better that I devote myself to studying
the other great mystery of the universe,

00:38:22.509 --> 00:38:23.718
women.

00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:29.390
Marty, Einie, brace yourselves
for temporal displacement.

00:38:34.562 --> 00:38:36.397
(ENGINE HUMMING)

00:38:39.776 --> 00:38:41.402
Did we make it?

00:38:45.323 --> 00:38:46.699
Are we back?

00:38:48.076 --> 00:38:49.577
(SCREAMING)

00:38:53.540 --> 00:38:54.582
We're back.

00:39:01.840 --> 00:39:03.466
(TIRES SCREECHING)

00:39:15.478 --> 00:39:16.855
Let's put her in the swing.

00:39:16.938 --> 00:39:20.233
Then I'll take you home, and you can
come back in your truck and wake her.

00:39:20.316 --> 00:39:22.777
When she awakens here in her own house
and it's dark,

00:39:22.861 --> 00:39:25.613
you should be able to convince her
that it was all a dream.

00:39:25.697 --> 00:39:28.449
Wait a minute. We're just gonna
leave her here on the porch?

00:39:28.533 --> 00:39:31.786
The disorientation will help convince her
that it was all a dream.

00:39:31.870 --> 00:39:33.746
How long do you think she's gonna be out?

00:39:33.830 --> 00:39:36.374
I'm not quite sure.
She received quite a shock.

00:39:36.457 --> 00:39:40.086
Could be for a few minutes.
Most probably, a couple of hours.

00:39:40.169 --> 00:39:41.880
You better bring smelling salts
back with you.

00:39:41.963 --> 00:39:43.256
You're the doc, Doc.

00:39:43.339 --> 00:39:44.382
All right. Come on. Let's go, Einie.

00:39:44.465 --> 00:39:45.925
(EINSTEIN WHIMPERING)

00:39:47.176 --> 00:39:49.220
Don't worry. She'll be fine.

00:39:50.305 --> 00:39:53.016
I don't remember bars
being on these windows.

00:39:59.856 --> 00:40:01.482
(DOGS GROWLING)

00:40:09.699 --> 00:40:12.785
If you need me, I'll be back at my lab
dismantling this thing.

00:40:12.869 --> 00:40:14.078
Right.

00:40:31.429 --> 00:40:33.097
What the hell?

00:40:49.238 --> 00:40:50.865
- (SCREAMING)
- (GASPS)

00:40:50.949 --> 00:40:52.659
Hey. Hey, wait. Wait a minute.

00:40:52.742 --> 00:40:54.452
(STUTTERING)
What are you doing in my room?

00:40:54.535 --> 00:40:56.704
- Help! Rape! Mom!
- Okay. Okay.

00:40:56.788 --> 00:40:59.582
- Dad, help!
- Freeze, sucker!

00:40:59.666 --> 00:41:01.209
- He jumped me!
- Hey, it's okay. I don't want any trouble.

00:41:01.292 --> 00:41:04.212
- He came through the window!
- You got trouble now, you piece of trash.

00:41:04.879 --> 00:41:06.214
What are you doing in here
with my daughter?

00:41:06.297 --> 00:41:10.218
- Hey, listen, I'm just in the wrong house.
- You got that right, you little son of a...

00:41:10.718 --> 00:41:14.722
- Hey, look, I made a mistake.
- Damn right you made a mistake!

00:41:14.806 --> 00:41:17.725
- BOY: Kill him!
- I'm gonna tear your ass up!

00:41:17.809 --> 00:41:19.936
That's right. You keep running, sucker!

00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:22.939
And you tell that realty company
that I ain't selling! You hear?

00:41:23.022 --> 00:41:24.983
We ain't gonna be terrorized!

00:41:35.284 --> 00:41:36.828
(DOGS HOWLING)

00:41:57.098 --> 00:41:59.559
(SIRENS WAILING)

00:42:07.108 --> 00:42:09.527
This has gotta be the wrong year.

00:42:22.123 --> 00:42:23.958
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

00:42:27.628 --> 00:42:29.005
1985?

00:42:30.548 --> 00:42:31.549
It can't be.

00:42:31.632 --> 00:42:32.675
- (GUN COCKING)
- STRICKLAND: Drop it.

00:42:36.471 --> 00:42:39.223
So you're the son of a bitch
who's been stealing my newspapers.

00:42:39.307 --> 00:42:40.683
Mr. Strickland.

00:42:41.225 --> 00:42:44.771
- Mr. Strickland. It's me, sir. It's Marty.
- Who?

00:42:44.854 --> 00:42:47.732
It's Marty McFly. Marty McFly.
Don't you know me, sir? From school, sir.

00:42:47.815 --> 00:42:50.860
I've never seen you before in my life,
but you look to me like a slacker.

00:42:50.943 --> 00:42:53.237
Yeah, that's right. That's right.
I am a slacker.

00:42:53.321 --> 00:42:55.406
Don't you remember?
You gave me detention last week.

00:42:55.490 --> 00:42:58.242
Last week?
The school burned down six years ago.

00:42:58.326 --> 00:43:01.079
Now, you got exactly three seconds
to get off my porch with your nuts intact.

00:43:01.162 --> 00:43:03.081
- One.
- Please, Mr. Strickland,

00:43:03.164 --> 00:43:04.582
I just want to know
what the hell's going on here.

00:43:04.665 --> 00:43:05.708
- Two.
- (SCREAMING)

00:43:05.792 --> 00:43:06.793
(TIRES SCREECHING)

00:43:06.876 --> 00:43:09.003
- Hey, Strickland!
- BOY: Yeah!

00:43:18.805 --> 00:43:20.181
(EXCLAIMING)

00:43:26.604 --> 00:43:28.356
Eat lead, slackers!

00:43:28.606 --> 00:43:29.982
(SCREAMING)

00:43:30.066 --> 00:43:31.567
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

00:43:35.446 --> 00:43:39.408
Watch where you're going,
crazy drunk pedestrian.

00:43:39.867 --> 00:43:41.202
Red.

00:44:37.550 --> 00:44:41.679
MAN: <i>Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the Biff Tannen Museum.</i>

00:44:41.762 --> 00:44:44.348
<i>Dedicated to Hill Valley's number one citizen</i>

00:44:44.432 --> 00:44:49.604
<i>and America's greatest living folk hero,
the one and only Biff Tannen.</i>

00:44:50.104 --> 00:44:53.774
<i>Of course, we've all heard the legend,
but who is the man?</i>

00:44:53.858 --> 00:44:55.109
<i>Inside, you will learn</i>

00:44:55.193 --> 00:44:59.197
<i>how Biff Tannen became one of the richest
and most powerful men in America.</i>

00:44:59.280 --> 00:45:01.949
<i>Learn the amazing history
of the Tannen family,</i>

00:45:02.033 --> 00:45:05.411
<i>starting with his great-grandfather,
Buford "Mad Dog" Tannen,</i>

00:45:05.494 --> 00:45:07.205
<i>fastest gun in the West.</i>

00:45:07.288 --> 00:45:10.458
<i>See Biff's humble beginnings
and how a trip to the racetrack</i>

00:45:10.541 --> 00:45:14.420
<i>on his 21st birthday
made him a millionaire overnight.</i>

00:45:15.379 --> 00:45:17.590
(BELL RINGING)

00:45:17.673 --> 00:45:20.426
<i>Share in the excitement
of a fabulous winning streak</i>

00:45:20.509 --> 00:45:24.305
<i>that earned him the nickname
"The Luckiest Man on Earth."</i>

00:45:24.388 --> 00:45:26.974
<i>Learn how Biff parlayed
that lucky winning streak</i>

00:45:27.058 --> 00:45:29.227
<i>into the vast empire called Biffco.</i>

00:45:29.310 --> 00:45:33.773
<i>Discover how in 1979, Biff successfully
lobbied to legalize gambling</i>

00:45:33.856 --> 00:45:36.525
<i>and turned
Hill Valley's dilapidated courthouse</i>

00:45:36.609 --> 00:45:39.237
<i>into a beautiful casino hotel.</i>

00:45:39.320 --> 00:45:43.074
<i>I just want to say one thing.
God bless America!</i>

00:45:43.991 --> 00:45:47.995
MAN: <i>Meet the women who shared
in his passion as he searched for true love,</i>

00:45:48.704 --> 00:45:50.414
<i>and relive Biff's happiest moment</i>

00:45:50.498 --> 00:45:54.085
<i>as, in 1973, he realized
his life-long romantic dream</i>

00:45:54.168 --> 00:45:57.129
<i>by marrying his high school sweetheart,
Lorraine Baines McFly.</i>

00:45:57.213 --> 00:45:59.966
- REPORTER: <i>How's it feel, Mr. Tannen?
- Third time's the charm.</i>

00:46:02.760 --> 00:46:07.139
No! No!

00:46:07.223 --> 00:46:09.600
- Hey, you're coming with us upstairs.
- Let me go.

00:46:09.684 --> 00:46:12.228
Look, sonny, we can do this the easy way
or the hard way.

00:46:12.770 --> 00:46:14.522
MAN: <i>The easy way.</i>

00:46:21.195 --> 00:46:25.866
- Mom? Mom, is that you?
- OLDER LORRAINE: Just relax, Marty.

00:46:26.742 --> 00:46:29.787
You've been asleep for almost two hours.

00:46:31.455 --> 00:46:34.709
I had a horrible nightmare. It was terrible.

00:46:35.167 --> 00:46:41.048
Well, you're safe and sound now,
back on the good old 27th floor.

00:46:42.008 --> 00:46:43.926
Twenty-seventh floor!

00:46:44.719 --> 00:46:45.720
(GASPS)

00:46:46.345 --> 00:46:48.222
(PANTING)

00:46:49.557 --> 00:46:52.351
Mom? Mom, that can't be you.

00:46:53.144 --> 00:46:56.147
Well, yes, it's me, Marty. Are you all right?

00:46:56.230 --> 00:47:00.151
I'm fine. I'm fine. It's just that you're so...
You're so

00:47:01.152 --> 00:47:02.403
big.

00:47:03.029 --> 00:47:05.489
Oh. Everything's gonna be fine, Marty.
Are you hungry?

00:47:05.573 --> 00:47:07.199
I can call room service.

00:47:07.283 --> 00:47:08.576
(GASPS)

00:47:09.243 --> 00:47:10.578
Room service?

00:47:10.661 --> 00:47:13.998
- OLDER BIFF: Lorraine!
- Oh, my God. It's your father.

00:47:14.081 --> 00:47:15.249
My father?

00:47:17.335 --> 00:47:20.087
You're supposed to be in Switzerland,
you little son of a bitch!

00:47:20.171 --> 00:47:21.339
My father!

00:47:21.422 --> 00:47:23.382
Did you get kicked out
of another boarding school?

00:47:23.466 --> 00:47:25.968
Damn it, Lorraine. Do you know
how much perfectly good dough

00:47:26.052 --> 00:47:28.763
I've blown on this no-good kid of yours,
huh? On all three of them?

00:47:28.846 --> 00:47:31.932
What the hell do you care? We can afford it.

00:47:32.475 --> 00:47:36.312
The least we can do with all that money
is provide a better life for our children.

00:47:36.395 --> 00:47:40.858
Hold on one second. Let's get this straight.
Marty is your kid, not mine.

00:47:40.941 --> 00:47:43.986
And all the money in the world
wouldn't do jack shit for that lazy bum.

00:47:44.070 --> 00:47:46.197
Stop it, Biff. Just stop it.

00:47:46.280 --> 00:47:49.742
Look at him.
He's a butthead, just like his old man was.

00:47:52.661 --> 00:47:56.290
Don't you dare speak that way about George.

00:47:57.875 --> 00:48:00.211
You're not even half the man he was.

00:48:00.878 --> 00:48:02.004
(GRUNTS)

00:48:02.088 --> 00:48:04.215
- You son of a bitch!
- Hey.

00:48:07.051 --> 00:48:08.552
(GROANING)

00:48:08.886 --> 00:48:11.222
OLDER BIFF: Always the little hothead, huh?

00:48:17.186 --> 00:48:19.313
You wanna take a poke at me?

00:48:21.232 --> 00:48:22.650
(MAN LAUGHING)

00:48:22.733 --> 00:48:25.528
Damn it, Biff. That's it. I'm leaving.

00:48:25.611 --> 00:48:26.612
(LAUGHS MOCKINGLY)

00:48:26.695 --> 00:48:29.323
So go ahead. But think about this, Lorraine!

00:48:29.490 --> 00:48:33.327
Who's gonna pay for all your clothes, huh?
And your jewelry and your liquor?

00:48:33.411 --> 00:48:36.580
Who's gonna pay
for your cosmetic surgery, Lorraine?

00:48:36.664 --> 00:48:40.042
You were the one
who wanted me to get these things.

00:48:40.668 --> 00:48:43.421
If you want them back, you can have them.

00:48:43.504 --> 00:48:45.798
Look, Lorraine. You walk out that door,

00:48:45.881 --> 00:48:48.926
and I won't only cut off you.
I'll cut off your kids.

00:48:49.677 --> 00:48:51.762
- You wouldn't.
- Wouldn't I?

00:48:51.846 --> 00:48:55.057
First your daughter, Linda.
I'll cancel all her credit cards.

00:48:55.141 --> 00:48:57.643
She can settle her debts
with the bank all by herself.

00:48:57.726 --> 00:49:00.855
Your idiot son, Dave.
I'll get his probation revoked.

00:49:00.938 --> 00:49:03.023
And as for Marty.

00:49:03.107 --> 00:49:05.943
Well, maybe you'd like to have
all three of your kids behind bars,

00:49:06.026 --> 00:49:08.112
just like your brother Joey.

00:49:08.195 --> 00:49:10.865
One big, happy, jailbird family.

00:49:13.617 --> 00:49:17.204
All right, Biff. You win. I'll stay.

00:49:20.875 --> 00:49:24.795
As for you, I'll be back up here in an hour,
so you better not be.

00:49:36.098 --> 00:49:38.684
He was right, and I was wrong.

00:49:41.061 --> 00:49:42.771
Mom!

00:49:42.855 --> 00:49:45.733
Mom, what are you saying?
You're actually defending him.

00:49:45.816 --> 00:49:50.279
I had it coming. He's my husband,
and he takes care of all of us,

00:49:50.905 --> 00:49:53.908
- and he deserves our respect.
- (YELLING) Respect?

00:49:54.658 --> 00:49:58.412
Your husband!
How could he be your husband?

00:49:58.954 --> 00:50:02.333
- How could you leave Dad for him?
- Leave Dad?

00:50:02.416 --> 00:50:07.004
- Marty, are you feeling all right?
- No. No, I'm not feeling all right!

00:50:07.087 --> 00:50:09.632
I don't understand one damn thing
that's going on around here,

00:50:09.715 --> 00:50:12.593
and why nobody can give me a simple,
straight answer.

00:50:12.843 --> 00:50:15.721
Oh, they must have
hit you over the head hard this time.

00:50:15.804 --> 00:50:18.891
Mom, I just want to know one thing.

00:50:18.974 --> 00:50:21.977
Where's my father? Where's George McFly?

00:50:23.437 --> 00:50:30.236
Marty, George, your father is in the same
place he's been for the past 12 years.

00:50:32.613 --> 00:50:34.573
Oak Park Cemetery.

00:50:34.657 --> 00:50:36.116
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

00:51:00.307 --> 00:51:01.642
No.

00:51:04.228 --> 00:51:06.981
No! This can't be happening!

00:51:08.065 --> 00:51:10.317
"March 15, 1973."

00:51:10.401 --> 00:51:13.571
No! Please, God, no!

00:51:15.030 --> 00:51:19.034
No, please, God. Please, God, no.
This can't be happening.

00:51:19.702 --> 00:51:21.120
This can't be happening.

00:51:22.830 --> 00:51:24.331
This can't be...

00:51:24.415 --> 00:51:26.875
I'm afraid it is happening, Marty. All of it.

00:51:27.334 --> 00:51:28.460
Doc!

00:51:28.544 --> 00:51:31.422
When I learned about your father,
I figured you'd come here.

00:51:31.505 --> 00:51:33.007
(WIND HOWLING)

00:51:33.966 --> 00:51:36.635
Then you know what happened to him?

00:51:38.137 --> 00:51:43.976
Do you know what happened
March 15, 1973?

00:51:45.894 --> 00:51:47.563
Yes, Marty. I know.

00:51:48.522 --> 00:51:51.483
DOC: I went to the public library
to try to make sense out of all the madness.

00:51:51.692 --> 00:51:53.152
The place was boarded up, shut down,

00:51:53.235 --> 00:51:55.154
so I broke in
and borrowed some newspapers.

00:51:55.237 --> 00:51:56.697
I don't get it, Doc.

00:51:56.905 --> 00:52:00.409
I mean, how can all this be happening?
It's like we're in hell or something.

00:52:00.492 --> 00:52:03.495
No, it's Hill Valley. Although,
I can't imagine hell being much worse.

00:52:03.579 --> 00:52:05.247
(EINSTEIN WHIMPERING)

00:52:05.581 --> 00:52:08.292
Oh, Einie. I'm sorry, boy.

00:52:09.043 --> 00:52:12.379
The lab is an awful, awful, awful,
awful mess.

00:52:13.672 --> 00:52:15.049
Attaboy.

00:52:15.758 --> 00:52:18.969
Obviously, the time continuum
has been disrupted,

00:52:19.053 --> 00:52:21.472
creating this new temporal event sequence

00:52:21.555 --> 00:52:24.433
- resulting in this alternate reality.
- English, Doc.

00:52:24.516 --> 00:52:26.810
Here, here, here. Let me illustrate.

00:52:31.523 --> 00:52:35.653
Imagine that this line represents time.

00:52:35.736 --> 00:52:40.532
Here's the present, 1985,
the future and the past.

00:52:42.284 --> 00:52:45.412
Prior to this point in time,
somewhere in the past,

00:52:45.496 --> 00:52:51.043
the timeline skewed into this tangent
creating an alternate 1985.

00:52:51.126 --> 00:52:54.922
Alternate to you, me and Einstein,

00:52:55.422 --> 00:52:58.467
but reality for everyone else.

00:53:02.763 --> 00:53:04.598
Recognize this?

00:53:04.848 --> 00:53:06.892
It's the bag the sports book came in.

00:53:06.975 --> 00:53:09.853
I know, because the receipt was still inside.

00:53:09.937 --> 00:53:13.857
I found them in the time machine
along with this.

00:53:19.446 --> 00:53:23.200
It's the top of Biff's cane.
I mean, Old Biff from the future.

00:53:23.283 --> 00:53:25.244
Correct. It was in the time machine

00:53:25.327 --> 00:53:29.623
because Biff was in the time machine
with the sports almanac.

00:53:30.290 --> 00:53:31.375
Holy shit.

00:53:31.458 --> 00:53:35.838
You see, while we were in the future,
Biff got the sports book,

00:53:35.921 --> 00:53:38.257
stole the time machine, went back in time,

00:53:38.340 --> 00:53:41.719
and gave the book to himself
at some point in the past.

00:53:42.010 --> 00:53:46.181
Look. It says right here

00:53:46.265 --> 00:53:51.478
that Biff made his first million
betting on a horse race in 1958.

00:53:52.104 --> 00:53:53.397
He wasn't just lucky.

00:53:53.480 --> 00:53:56.984
He knew because he had all the race results
in the sports almanac.

00:53:57.234 --> 00:53:59.945
That's how he made his entire fortune.

00:54:00.654 --> 00:54:02.990
Look at his pocket with a magnifying glass.

00:54:05.451 --> 00:54:06.994
The almanac.

00:54:07.828 --> 00:54:10.205
Son of a bitch stole my idea.

00:54:11.039 --> 00:54:13.333
He must have been listening when I...

00:54:15.294 --> 00:54:18.505
It's my fault. The whole thing is my fault.

00:54:18.589 --> 00:54:22.217
If I hadn't bought that damn book,
none of this would have ever happened.

00:54:22.301 --> 00:54:24.595
- Well, it's all in the past.
- You mean the future?

00:54:24.678 --> 00:54:29.433
Whatever. It demonstrates precisely
how time travel can be misused

00:54:29.516 --> 00:54:32.644
and why the time machine
must be destroyed

00:54:32.728 --> 00:54:35.105
after we straighten all of this out.

00:54:35.189 --> 00:54:37.274
Right. So we go back to the future,

00:54:37.357 --> 00:54:39.485
and we stop Biff
from stealing the time machine.

00:54:39.568 --> 00:54:44.656
We can't, because if we travel
into the future from this point in time,

00:54:44.740 --> 00:54:48.285
it will be the future of this reality,

00:54:49.077 --> 00:54:54.249
in which Biff is corrupt and powerful
and married to your mother

00:54:54.333 --> 00:54:59.213
and in which this has happened to me.

00:55:00.047 --> 00:55:01.173
(WHIMPERING)

00:55:04.718 --> 00:55:09.598
No. Our only chance to repair the present
is in the past

00:55:09.681 --> 00:55:13.811
at the point where the timeline
skewed into this tangent.

00:55:13.894 --> 00:55:17.981
In order to put the universe back
as we remember it

00:55:18.065 --> 00:55:20.400
and get back to our reality,

00:55:20.484 --> 00:55:24.196
we have to find out the exact date
and the specific circumstances

00:55:24.279 --> 00:55:29.618
of how, where and when Young Biff
got his hands on that sports almanac.

00:55:32.412 --> 00:55:33.580
I'll ask him.

00:55:57.229 --> 00:56:01.400
Bulletproof vest! (LAUGHS) Great flick!
Great frigging flick!

00:56:01.692 --> 00:56:03.777
The guy is brilliant.

00:56:04.278 --> 00:56:05.946
Hey, what the hell's going...

00:56:06.029 --> 00:56:08.532
- (GIRLS SCREAMING)
- Hey! What the hell are you doing in here?

00:56:08.615 --> 00:56:09.783
Party's over, Biff.

00:56:11.660 --> 00:56:12.953
Sorry, ladies.

00:56:13.036 --> 00:56:15.789
How did you get past
my security downstairs?

00:56:16.456 --> 00:56:18.166
There's a little matter we need to talk about.

00:56:18.250 --> 00:56:22.546
- Yeah. Money, right? Well, forget it.
- No. Not money.

00:56:24.464 --> 00:56:27.926
<i>Gray's Sports Almanac.</i>

00:56:31.346 --> 00:56:33.307
You heard him, girls.

00:56:33.807 --> 00:56:35.267
Party's over.

00:56:36.476 --> 00:56:39.980
Start talking, kid.
What else you know about that book?

00:56:41.690 --> 00:56:44.484
First, you tell me how you got it.

00:56:44.985 --> 00:56:48.238
How, where and when.

00:56:48.906 --> 00:56:50.157
(SCOFFS)

00:56:50.657 --> 00:56:52.993
All right. Take a seat.

00:56:56.997 --> 00:56:58.332
Sit down!

00:57:02.502 --> 00:57:05.297
November 12, 1955. That was when.

00:57:05.380 --> 00:57:08.550
November 12, 1955.
That was the date I went back...

00:57:09.843 --> 00:57:13.889
That was the date
of the famous Hill Valley lightning storm.

00:57:15.057 --> 00:57:17.726
You know your history. Very good.

00:57:18.685 --> 00:57:20.437
I'll never forget that Saturday.

00:57:20.520 --> 00:57:22.230
I'd just picked my car up from the shop,

00:57:22.314 --> 00:57:25.484
'cause I'd rolled it in a drag race
a few days earlier.

00:57:25.567 --> 00:57:28.195
I thought you crashed into a manure truck.

00:57:29.571 --> 00:57:32.157
How do you know about that?

00:57:32.240 --> 00:57:35.369
- My father told me about it.
- Your father?

00:57:36.620 --> 00:57:38.538
Before he died.

00:57:39.581 --> 00:57:41.083
Yeah. Right.

00:57:42.292 --> 00:57:45.170
So there I was, minding my own business.

00:57:45.253 --> 00:57:48.548
This crazy old codger with a cane shows up.

00:57:48.632 --> 00:57:52.386
He says he's my distant relative.
I don't see any resemblance.

00:57:54.388 --> 00:57:57.224
So he says,
"How would you like to be rich?"

00:57:57.808 --> 00:57:59.685
So I said, "Sure."

00:58:04.439 --> 00:58:06.483
So he lays this book on me.

00:58:06.566 --> 00:58:08.318
He says this book will tell me the outcome

00:58:08.402 --> 00:58:11.071
of every sporting event
till the end of the century.

00:58:11.154 --> 00:58:14.616
All I have to do is bet on the winner,
and I'll never lose.

00:58:17.828 --> 00:58:22.541
So I said, "What's the catch?"
He says, "No catch. Just keep it a secret."

00:58:25.502 --> 00:58:26.545
(SIGHS)

00:58:26.628 --> 00:58:30.590
After that, he disappeared.
I never saw him again.

00:58:43.311 --> 00:58:45.522
Oh, and he told me one more thing.

00:58:45.605 --> 00:58:48.358
He said, "Someday a crazy,
wild-eyed scientist,

00:58:48.442 --> 00:58:51.903
"or a kid may show up
asking about that book.

00:58:51.987 --> 00:58:54.197
"And if that ever happens..."

00:58:57.284 --> 00:58:58.618
(CHUCKLES)

00:58:59.286 --> 00:59:02.622
Funny. I never thought it would be you.

00:59:03.540 --> 00:59:05.250
Yeah, well, Biff, you're forgetting one thing.

00:59:05.333 --> 00:59:07.127
What the hell is that?

00:59:12.966 --> 00:59:16.011
You're dead, you little son of a bitch!

00:59:24.936 --> 00:59:26.480
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

00:59:28.231 --> 00:59:30.525
- Hey, there he is!
- Hey, hey!

00:59:41.411 --> 00:59:42.829
(THUGS YELLING)

00:59:45.457 --> 00:59:46.750
Oh, yeah!

01:00:12.734 --> 01:00:15.403
Go ahead, kid. Jump.

01:00:16.154 --> 01:00:18.949
A suicide will be nice and neat.

01:00:19.032 --> 01:00:20.700
What if I don't?

01:00:21.618 --> 01:00:23.370
Lead poisoning.

01:00:23.453 --> 01:00:25.330
What about the police, Biff?

01:00:25.413 --> 01:00:27.874
They're gonna match up the bullet
with that gun.

01:00:27.958 --> 01:00:30.043
Kid, I own the police.

01:00:32.045 --> 01:00:36.383
Besides, they couldn't match up
the bullet that killed your old man.

01:00:36.842 --> 01:00:38.218
You son of a...

01:00:40.679 --> 01:00:43.098
I suppose it's poetic justice.

01:00:43.932 --> 01:00:48.061
Two McFlys with the same gun.

01:00:59.406 --> 01:01:00.407
Idiot.

01:01:03.702 --> 01:01:05.328
(ENGINE WHIRRING)

01:01:05.412 --> 01:01:06.663
What the hell?

01:01:08.248 --> 01:01:09.332
(GROANS)

01:01:11.626 --> 01:01:13.128
Nice shot, Doc!

01:01:14.671 --> 01:01:18.258
You're not gonna believe this.
We gotta go back to 1955.

01:01:18.341 --> 01:01:20.010
I don't believe it.

01:01:31.605 --> 01:01:33.857
MARTY: That's right, Doc. November 12, 1955.

01:01:33.940 --> 01:01:37.527
Unbelievable that Old Biff
could've chosen that particular date.

01:01:37.611 --> 01:01:38.653
It could mean that that point in time

01:01:38.737 --> 01:01:41.364
inherently contains
some sort of cosmic significance,

01:01:41.448 --> 01:01:43.366
almost as if it were
the temporal junction point

01:01:43.450 --> 01:01:45.619
for the entire space-time continuum.

01:01:45.702 --> 01:01:48.580
On the other hand,
it could just be an amazing coincidence.

01:01:48.788 --> 01:01:50.123
(BEEPING)

01:01:51.374 --> 01:01:55.503
Damn! Got to fix that thing.
All right. Time circuits on.

01:01:56.546 --> 01:01:58.632
What do you mean, time circuits on?

01:01:58.715 --> 01:02:01.468
- Doc, we're not going back now.
- Yep.

01:02:01.551 --> 01:02:03.303
Doc, what about Jennifer?
What about Einstein?

01:02:03.386 --> 01:02:04.763
We can't just leave them here.

01:02:04.846 --> 01:02:06.973
Don't worry, Marty.
Assuming we succeed in our mission,

01:02:07.057 --> 01:02:10.560
this alternate 1985 will be changed
back into the real 1985,

01:02:10.644 --> 01:02:13.897
instantaneously transforming
around Jennifer and Einie.

01:02:13.980 --> 01:02:15.523
Jennifer and Einie will be fine,

01:02:15.607 --> 01:02:18.360
and they will have absolutely no memory
of this horrible place.

01:02:18.485 --> 01:02:19.903
Doc.

01:02:20.487 --> 01:02:22.322
What if we don't succeed?

01:02:23.073 --> 01:02:24.491
We must succeed.

01:02:38.922 --> 01:02:42.425
This is heavy, Doc.
I mean, it's like I was just here yesterday.

01:02:42.509 --> 01:02:45.595
You were here yesterday, Marty.
You were. Amazing, isn't it?

01:02:45.679 --> 01:02:48.848
All right, sunrise should be
in about 22 minutes.

01:02:48.932 --> 01:02:52.227
You go into town.
Track down Young Biff and tail him.

01:02:52.310 --> 01:02:56.439
Sometime today, Old Biff will show up
to give Young Biff the almanac.

01:02:56.523 --> 01:02:58.608
Above all you, must not interfere
with that event.

01:02:58.692 --> 01:03:01.653
We must let Old Biff believe he's succeeded,
so that he'll leave 1955

01:03:01.736 --> 01:03:04.114
- and bring the DeLorean back to the future.
- Right.

01:03:04.197 --> 01:03:07.325
Once Old Biff is gone,
grab the almanac any way that you can.

01:03:07.409 --> 01:03:09.577
Remember, both of our futures
depend on this.

01:03:09.661 --> 01:03:11.621
You don't have to remind me of that, Doc.

01:03:11.705 --> 01:03:16.293
Here's some binoculars and a walkie-talkie
so we can keep in contact.

01:03:16.376 --> 01:03:19.421
I'll stay here and try to repair the short
in the time circuit.

01:03:19.504 --> 01:03:22.299
That way, we don't risk anyone else
stealing the time machine,

01:03:22.382 --> 01:03:26.678
and I won't risk
accidentally running into my other self.

01:03:26.761 --> 01:03:30.015
- Other self?
- Yes. There are now two of me here,

01:03:30.098 --> 01:03:31.975
and there are two of you here.

01:03:32.058 --> 01:03:36.146
The other me is
the Dr. Emmett Brown from 1955,

01:03:36.229 --> 01:03:41.192
the younger me that helps the other you
get back to 1985.

01:03:41.943 --> 01:03:43.570
Remember the lightning bolt
at the clock tower?

01:03:43.653 --> 01:03:45.655
- Yeah.
- That event doesn't happen until tonight,

01:03:45.739 --> 01:03:48.325
so you must be very careful
not to run into your other self.

01:03:48.408 --> 01:03:49.576
Let me give you some money.

01:03:51.453 --> 01:03:52.620
(MARTY WHISTLES)

01:03:53.413 --> 01:03:56.666
I have to be prepared
for all monetary possibilities.

01:03:56.750 --> 01:03:59.711
- Get yourself some '50s clothes.
- Check, Doc.

01:04:00.920 --> 01:04:02.756
Something inconspicuous.

01:04:04.007 --> 01:04:06.676
Doc. Come in, Doc. This is Marty. Over.

01:04:06.760 --> 01:04:08.970
DOC ON RADIO: <i>Roger, Marty.
This is Doc. Are you there?</i>

01:04:09.054 --> 01:04:12.515
Yeah, Doc. I'm at the address.

01:04:12.599 --> 01:04:15.935
It's the only Tannen in the book,
but I don't think this is Biff's house.

01:04:16.019 --> 01:04:17.896
It looks like some old lady lives here.

01:04:17.979 --> 01:04:19.647
- WOMAN: Biff!
- Yeah.

01:04:20.148 --> 01:04:24.277
- Where are you going, Biff?
- I'm going to get my car, Grandma.

01:04:24.361 --> 01:04:28.031
When are you coming back? My feet hurt,
and I want you to rub my toes some more.

01:04:28.114 --> 01:04:30.116
Shut up, you old bag.

01:04:30.200 --> 01:04:32.535
KIDS: Give us our ball back.

01:04:32.619 --> 01:04:34.412
- What ball?
- That ball!

01:04:34.496 --> 01:04:36.539
What ball are you talking about?

01:04:36.623 --> 01:04:38.291
KIDS: Give us our ball!

01:04:38.375 --> 01:04:40.126
- What ball?
- Biff!

01:04:40.335 --> 01:04:42.045
- Is this your ball?
- KIDS: Yeah!

01:04:42.128 --> 01:04:45.131
- Is it your ball? You want it back?
- KIDS: Yeah.

01:04:46.800 --> 01:04:48.218
Go get it.

01:04:48.301 --> 01:04:49.636
(LAUGHING)

01:04:51.846 --> 01:04:56.142
Doc, it is Biff's house. I'm on him. Over.

01:05:04.317 --> 01:05:05.443
Hey.

01:05:08.113 --> 01:05:09.239
Looking good, Terry.

01:05:09.322 --> 01:05:12.617
Hey, Biff, she's all fixed up just like new,
but I couldn't get her started.

01:05:12.700 --> 01:05:14.536
You got some kind of kill switch
on this thing?

01:05:14.619 --> 01:05:18.123
No, you just gotta have the right touch.
Nobody can start this car but me.

01:05:18.206 --> 01:05:21.376
- Yeah, the bill comes to $302.57.
- 300 bucks?

01:05:21.459 --> 01:05:24.504
300 bucks for a couple of dents?
No, hey, that's bullshit, Terry.

01:05:24.587 --> 01:05:25.797
No, Biff, it was horse shit.

01:05:25.880 --> 01:05:27.006
- The whole car was full of it.
- (CHUCKLES)

01:05:27.090 --> 01:05:29.134
We had to pay Old Man Jones 80 bucks
to haul it away.

01:05:29.217 --> 01:05:30.552
BIFF: Old Man Jones probably resold it, too.

01:05:30.635 --> 01:05:32.971
- Now I ought to get something for that.
- You want something for it?

01:05:33.054 --> 01:05:35.974
We'll go inside. You can call Old Man Jones.
If he wants to give you a refund...

01:05:36.057 --> 01:05:41.271
It's 300 bucks, Terry. If I catch the guy
that caused this, I'll break his neck.

01:05:41.688 --> 01:05:44.566
The manure. I remember that.

01:05:51.114 --> 01:05:53.116
Four cans of Valvoline is fair, Biff.

01:05:53.199 --> 01:05:56.286
- Four cans for a $300 job?
- I couldn't even have lunch in the shop.

01:05:56.369 --> 01:05:57.620
- Makes me nauseous.
- I should get a case of oil

01:05:57.704 --> 01:05:59.539
- out of you for a 300 buck job.
- You've been inside.

01:05:59.622 --> 01:06:01.291
It smells worse than the bathroom
at a gas station.

01:06:01.374 --> 01:06:02.625
- (GROANS)
- You robbed me again, Terry. Yeah, yeah.

01:06:02.709 --> 01:06:04.502
The smell's never gonna go away, Biff.

01:06:04.586 --> 01:06:05.628
Never gonna go away.

01:06:05.712 --> 01:06:07.255
- Last time I do you a favor. Last time.
- Thanks a lot.

01:06:07.338 --> 01:06:08.756
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

01:06:09.716 --> 01:06:10.717
Let me see.

01:06:11.551 --> 01:06:13.094
(EXCLAIMS)

01:06:14.888 --> 01:06:16.639
BABS: It's perfect, Lorraine.

01:06:16.723 --> 01:06:19.559
- LORRAINE: Oh, look at it!
- You're going to look so good!

01:06:24.439 --> 01:06:27.150
- You're going to look...
- Well, lookey what we have here.

01:06:27.233 --> 01:06:28.318
Hey, nice dress, Lorraine.

01:06:28.401 --> 01:06:30.820
Although, I think you'd look better
wearing nothing at all.

01:06:30.904 --> 01:06:33.781
Biff, why don't you take a long walk
off a short pier?

01:06:33.865 --> 01:06:36.326
BIFF: Hey, listen, Lorraine.
There's that dance at school tonight, right.

01:06:36.409 --> 01:06:38.870
Now that my car's all fixed,
I figure I'd cut you a break

01:06:38.953 --> 01:06:41.706
and give you the honor of going
with the best-looking guy in school.

01:06:41.789 --> 01:06:42.832
Yeah, well, I'm busy.

01:06:42.916 --> 01:06:44.501
- Yeah, doing what?
- Washing my hair.

01:06:44.584 --> 01:06:47.253
That's about as funny
as a screen door on a battleship.

01:06:47.337 --> 01:06:49.380
Screen door on a submarine, you dork.

01:06:49.464 --> 01:06:52.091
Look, Biff, somebody already asked me
to the dance.

01:06:52.675 --> 01:06:55.011
Who? That bug George McFly?

01:06:55.470 --> 01:06:59.933
- I'm going with Calvin Klein, okay?
- Calvin Klein? No, it's not okay.

01:07:00.558 --> 01:07:03.561
- You're going with me, understand?
- Get your cooties off me!

01:07:03.645 --> 01:07:05.813
When are you gonna get it through
your thick skull, Lorraine?

01:07:05.897 --> 01:07:07.190
You're my girl.

01:07:07.273 --> 01:07:11.819
Biff Tannen, I wouldn't be your girl
even if you had a million dollars!

01:07:12.654 --> 01:07:13.947
(GROANS)

01:07:15.448 --> 01:07:17.867
Yes, you will! It's you and me, Lorraine.

01:07:17.951 --> 01:07:18.910
(HORN HONKING)

01:07:18.993 --> 01:07:20.245
Watch it!

01:07:20.328 --> 01:07:22.121
It's meant to be.

01:07:22.205 --> 01:07:26.376
I'm going to marry you someday, Lorraine.
Someday you'll be my wife!

01:07:29.629 --> 01:07:32.131
You always did have a way with women.

01:07:32.215 --> 01:07:34.217
Get the hell out of my car, old man.

01:07:34.300 --> 01:07:37.220
You want to marry that girl, Biff?
I can help make it happen.

01:07:37.303 --> 01:07:39.389
Oh, yeah? Who are you, Miss Lonely-Hearts?

01:07:39.472 --> 01:07:42.267
Just get in the car, butthead.

01:07:42.350 --> 01:07:44.769
- (STARTS ENGINE)
- Who are you calling butthead, butthead?

01:07:45.478 --> 01:07:49.148
How do you know how to do that?
Nobody can start this car but me.

01:07:49.232 --> 01:07:52.777
Just get in the car, Tannen.
Today's your lucky day.

01:07:53.027 --> 01:07:54.445
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:07:55.363 --> 01:07:58.992
Hey! Hey!
Hey, watch where you're driving, old man.

01:07:59.534 --> 01:08:01.077
If you dent this car, I'll kill you.

01:08:03.454 --> 01:08:04.789
(EXCLAIMING)

01:08:07.834 --> 01:08:11.754
- This cost me 300 bucks!
- Would you shut up about the car?

01:08:12.213 --> 01:08:14.132
Hey, and another thing.
How do you know where I live?

01:08:14.215 --> 01:08:16.426
Let's just say we're related, Biff.

01:08:16.509 --> 01:08:19.053
And that being the case,
I got a little present for you.

01:08:19.137 --> 01:08:21.264
Something that'll make you rich.

01:08:21.347 --> 01:08:25.351
- You want to be rich, don't you?
- Oh, yeah. Sure. Right. That's rich. (LAUGHS)

01:08:25.435 --> 01:08:27.353
You're going to make me rich?

01:08:27.895 --> 01:08:31.107
You see this book?
This book tells the future.

01:08:31.190 --> 01:08:34.485
Tells the results of every major sports event
till the end of the century.

01:08:34.569 --> 01:08:38.531
Football, baseball, horse races, boxing.

01:08:39.657 --> 01:08:43.453
The information in here is worth millions,
and I'm giving it to you.

01:08:43.536 --> 01:08:46.122
Well, that's very nice. Thank you very much.

01:08:46.205 --> 01:08:50.043
Now, why don't you make like a tree
and get out of here?

01:08:51.044 --> 01:08:54.797
It's leave, you idiot.
Make like a tree and leave.

01:08:54.881 --> 01:08:57.091
You sound like a damn fool
when you say it wrong.

01:08:57.175 --> 01:09:01.054
All right, then, leave
and take your book with you.

01:09:01.137 --> 01:09:04.807
Don't you get it?
You could make a fortune with this book.

01:09:04.891 --> 01:09:06.351
Let me show you.

01:09:07.644 --> 01:09:09.062
(STATIC)

01:09:10.647 --> 01:09:13.358
MAN ON RADIO: <i>UCLA trails 17-16.</i>

01:09:13.441 --> 01:09:16.778
<i>It's 4th and 11
with only 18 seconds left of this game.</i>

01:09:16.861 --> 01:09:19.989
<i>I'd say it's all over for UCLA.</i>

01:09:20.073 --> 01:09:23.826
Bet you a million bucks UCLA wins it 19-17.

01:09:23.910 --> 01:09:27.497
What are you, deaf, old man?
He just said it was over. You lost.

01:09:27.580 --> 01:09:29.040
Oh, yeah?

01:09:29.499 --> 01:09:30.833
- (VOLUME INCREASING)
<i>- Here comes Decker with the kick.</i>

01:09:30.917 --> 01:09:32.418
<i>It's up. It looks good, folks!</i>

01:09:32.502 --> 01:09:36.798
<i>It looks very good. Field goal!
UCLA wins 19-17.</i>

01:09:37.090 --> 01:09:41.010
<i>Listen to that Coliseum crowd go wild.
Jim Decker...</i>

01:09:41.094 --> 01:09:42.345
All right, pops. What's the gag?

01:09:42.428 --> 01:09:44.347
How did you know
what the score was gonna be?

01:09:44.430 --> 01:09:46.641
I told you. It's in this book.

01:09:46.724 --> 01:09:50.269
All you gotta do is bet on the winner,
and you'll never lose.

01:09:55.858 --> 01:09:58.444
All right. I'll take a look at it.

01:10:00.863 --> 01:10:02.949
OLDEST BIFF: You damn fool!

01:10:03.032 --> 01:10:05.952
Never, never leave this book laying around.

01:10:06.035 --> 01:10:08.955
Don't you have a safe?
No, you don't have a safe.

01:10:10.123 --> 01:10:14.919
Get a safe. Keep it locked up.
And until then, keep it on you like this.

01:10:15.002 --> 01:10:17.964
- Hey, what are you doing?
- And don't tell anybody about it, either.

01:10:18.047 --> 01:10:23.219
And there's one more thing.
One day, a kid or a crazy, wild-eyed old man

01:10:23.302 --> 01:10:27.390
who claims to be a scientist
is going to come around asking about this...

01:10:27.473 --> 01:10:29.225
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

01:10:30.017 --> 01:10:32.311
If that ever happens...

01:10:49.203 --> 01:10:50.997
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:10:51.998 --> 01:10:54.292
I'm trapped. Doc.

01:10:54.500 --> 01:10:55.668
<i>Doc, come in, Doc.</i>

01:10:55.752 --> 01:10:57.587
- Marty, what's the report?
<i>- Biff's gone.</i>

01:10:58.129 --> 01:11:01.382
He's got the book. The old man's gone, too.
I'm locked in Biff's garage.

01:11:01.466 --> 01:11:03.843
<i>You gotta fly the DeLorean over here
and get me the hell out of here.</i>

01:11:04.177 --> 01:11:05.928
The address is 1809 Mason Street.

01:11:06.012 --> 01:11:07.930
I can't take the DeLorean out in the daylight,

01:11:08.014 --> 01:11:09.932
but don't worry, Marty.
Somehow I'll get over there.

01:11:10.016 --> 01:11:13.352
Doc, wait a minute. Doc. Hey, Doc. Doc.

01:11:14.937 --> 01:11:16.355
Perfect.

01:11:23.279 --> 01:11:26.115
I told you, Grandma. I'm going to the dance.

01:11:26.199 --> 01:11:28.159
- WOMAN: When you coming home?
- The dance.

01:11:28.242 --> 01:11:30.995
BIFF: I'll get home when I get home.

01:11:32.288 --> 01:11:35.208
Don't forget to turn off the garage light.

01:11:40.713 --> 01:11:41.923
(ENGINE STARTING)

01:11:50.181 --> 01:11:51.599
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:11:52.683 --> 01:11:54.018
(BICYCLE BELL RINGING)

01:12:07.156 --> 01:12:08.783
Marty. Marty!

01:12:09.242 --> 01:12:10.660
Marty.

01:12:12.662 --> 01:12:15.122
Marty, Marty. Damn!

01:12:15.915 --> 01:12:18.000
Where is that kid?

01:12:18.084 --> 01:12:19.794
(MUSIC PLAYING ON CAR STEREO)

01:12:24.340 --> 01:12:26.425
Doc. Doc, come in.

01:12:27.093 --> 01:12:28.636
<i>Come in, Doc.</i>

01:12:29.387 --> 01:12:30.471
Marty! Marty, come in.

01:12:30.763 --> 01:12:31.973
- Doc.
- (FEEDBACK)

01:12:35.810 --> 01:12:37.103
Marty.

01:12:38.145 --> 01:12:39.772
Oh, my...

01:12:41.440 --> 01:12:43.442
Great Scott.

01:12:59.041 --> 01:13:00.418
Oh, my God.

01:13:05.631 --> 01:13:06.757
Doc, Doc, come in.

01:13:06.841 --> 01:13:10.094
Marty, what happened to you?
I went to Biff's house, and you weren't there.

01:13:10.177 --> 01:13:12.346
You must have just missed me.
I'm in the back of Biff's car.

01:13:12.430 --> 01:13:14.473
He's on his way
to the Enchantment Under the Sea dance.

01:13:15.391 --> 01:13:17.393
Marty, listen, we may have
to abort this entire plan.

01:13:17.476 --> 01:13:18.895
It's getting much too dangerous.

01:13:18.978 --> 01:13:20.563
Don't worry.
The book is on Biff's dashboard.

01:13:20.646 --> 01:13:21.981
I'll grab it as soon as we get to the school.

01:13:22.064 --> 01:13:25.610
Marty, you must be extremely careful
not to run into your other self.

01:13:25.693 --> 01:13:27.320
<i>- My other self?</i>
- Yes.

01:13:28.029 --> 01:13:32.158
Remember, your mother is
at that exact same dance with you. Yeah.

01:13:32.241 --> 01:13:35.661
<i>- Right. This could get heavy, Doc.</i>
- Heavy, heavy.

01:13:35.745 --> 01:13:38.372
Marty, whatever happens,
you must not let your other self see you!

01:13:38.456 --> 01:13:42.043
- The consequences could be disastrous.
- Excuse me, sir.

01:13:42.126 --> 01:13:43.127
(GASPS)

01:13:43.210 --> 01:13:44.754
Yes, you with the hat.

01:13:44.837 --> 01:13:47.048
- Who, me?
- Yes.

01:13:47.423 --> 01:13:51.177
Be a pal and hand me a five-eighths inch
wrench out of that toolbox.

01:13:52.261 --> 01:13:53.846
Five-eighths?

01:13:55.514 --> 01:13:57.934
Don't you mean three-quarters?

01:13:58.684 --> 01:14:00.770
Why, you're right.

01:14:01.562 --> 01:14:06.192
I presume you're conducting
some sort of weather experiment.

01:14:08.194 --> 01:14:11.280
That's right. How did you know that?

01:14:11.364 --> 01:14:15.326
I happen to have had a little experience
in this area.

01:14:15.409 --> 01:14:18.079
Yes, well, I'm hoping
to see some lightning tonight.

01:14:18.162 --> 01:14:21.207
Although, the weatherman says
there's not gonna be any rain.

01:14:21.290 --> 01:14:24.877
There's going to be plenty of rain, all right.
Wind, thunder, lightning.

01:14:24.961 --> 01:14:29.548
- It's gonna be one hell of a storm.
- Well, thanks. Nice talking to you.

01:14:29.632 --> 01:14:33.469
Maybe we'll bump into each other some time
again in the future.

01:14:34.470 --> 01:14:36.097
Or in the past.

01:14:46.899 --> 01:14:48.401
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:14:53.781 --> 01:14:55.574
(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

01:15:17.179 --> 01:15:18.931
Doc, Doc! Come in!

01:15:33.529 --> 01:15:34.947
(GIRLS EXCLAIMING)

01:16:32.171 --> 01:16:34.965
BIFF: Where's that punk
Calvin Klein, anyway?

01:16:35.049 --> 01:16:37.259
BOY: How am I supposed to know, Biff?
I ain't his secretary. (LAUGHING)

01:16:37.343 --> 01:16:40.262
Well, go find him.
He caused 300 bucks damage to my car,

01:16:40.346 --> 01:16:42.890
and I owe him a knuckle sandwich.
Get going!

01:16:42.973 --> 01:16:44.266
- Drink up, Biff.
- Yeah, thanks.

01:16:44.350 --> 01:16:46.644
- Ain't you coming?
- I'm reading.

01:16:48.187 --> 01:16:49.730
(BOTTLE BREAKING)

01:17:39.238 --> 01:17:41.448
Well, well, well, Mr. Tannen.

01:17:42.575 --> 01:17:44.326
How nice to see you here.

01:17:44.410 --> 01:17:48.956
- Why, Mr. Strickland, it's nice to see you, sir.
- Is that liquor I smell, Tannen?

01:17:49.498 --> 01:17:51.000
(STUTTERING) I wouldn't know.

01:17:51.083 --> 01:17:53.627
I don't know what liquor smells like,
'cause I'm too young to drink it.

01:17:53.711 --> 01:17:55.045
I see.

01:17:55.504 --> 01:17:57.381
And what have we here?

01:18:00.926 --> 01:18:04.430
Sports statistics, interesting subject.
Homework, Tannen?

01:18:04.513 --> 01:18:07.349
No, it ain't homework, 'cause I ain't at home.

01:18:07.433 --> 01:18:08.809
(CHUCKLES)

01:18:09.435 --> 01:18:12.229
You've got a real attitude problem.
You know that, Tannen? Just watch it.

01:18:12.313 --> 01:18:15.900
Because one day, I'll have you
right where I want you in detention.

01:18:15.983 --> 01:18:17.109
Slacker!

01:18:29.955 --> 01:18:31.916
MARTY: Jesus, you smoke, too?

01:18:31.999 --> 01:18:34.752
LORRAINE: Marty, you're beginning
to sound just like my mother.

01:18:34.835 --> 01:18:36.253
Yeah, right.

01:18:36.337 --> 01:18:39.632
When I have kids,
I'm going to let them do anything they want.

01:18:39.715 --> 01:18:41.217
Anything at all.

01:18:41.300 --> 01:18:44.220
- Yeah, I'd like to have that in writing.
- Yeah, me, too.

01:18:44.303 --> 01:18:47.056
Marty, why are you so nervous?

01:19:42.361 --> 01:19:43.529
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:20:52.264 --> 01:20:53.432
Yes!

01:20:57.227 --> 01:20:58.312
No!

01:21:01.106 --> 01:21:02.608
<i>"Oh Là Là?"</i>

01:21:03.442 --> 01:21:04.943
<i>"Oh Là Là?"</i>

01:21:07.112 --> 01:21:08.530
<i>"Oh Là Là?"</i>

01:21:10.949 --> 01:21:12.201
(ANXIOUS GASPING)

01:21:14.286 --> 01:21:16.872
- Doc! Doc!
- Hey, you.

01:21:16.955 --> 01:21:19.875
- Doc, come in!
- DOC: <i>Marty, what's up?</i>

01:21:19.958 --> 01:21:22.461
Doc! I'm in trouble. I blew it.

01:21:22.544 --> 01:21:24.963
- Where's the book?
<i>- Biff must still have it with him.</i>

01:21:25.130 --> 01:21:27.758
- All I got is the damn cover.
<i>- And where's Biff?</i>

01:21:27.841 --> 01:21:29.885
- You're asking for it.
- I don't know.

01:21:29.968 --> 01:21:33.680
<i>- Don't you have any idea where he is?</i>
- No! I mean, he could be anywhere by now.

01:21:33.764 --> 01:21:37.393
Marty, the entire future depends on you
finding Biff and getting that book back!

01:21:37.476 --> 01:21:40.396
- I know. I just don't know where...
- LORRAINE: Stop it!

01:21:40.479 --> 01:21:43.982
Stop it, Biff. You'll break his arm. Stop it!

01:21:48.070 --> 01:21:49.488
Of course!

01:21:50.155 --> 01:21:54.326
I gotta go. I got one chance!
My old man is about to deck Biff!

01:22:01.750 --> 01:22:02.960
Yes!

01:22:16.265 --> 01:22:17.850
Talk about déjà vu.

01:22:18.100 --> 01:22:19.726
Are you okay?

01:22:39.538 --> 01:22:43.667
Okay, everybody, let's back up now.
Let's back up. Let's everybody just back up

01:22:43.750 --> 01:22:46.211
and give him a little bit of room, okay.
A little bit of air.

01:22:46.295 --> 01:22:50.424
- It's okay. I know CPR. I know CPR.
- Hey.

01:22:50.507 --> 01:22:53.051
- What's CPR?
- You!

01:22:56.889 --> 01:22:59.975
- He's fine.
- Hey, did you just take his wallet?

01:23:00.058 --> 01:23:01.768
He just took that guy's wallet.

01:23:02.227 --> 01:23:04.646
MARTY: <i>Doc, success. I got it.</i>

01:23:04.730 --> 01:23:06.648
Thank goodness.

01:23:07.649 --> 01:23:09.318
Great, Marty.

01:23:09.401 --> 01:23:11.320
As soon as I reload the fusion generator,

01:23:11.403 --> 01:23:13.780
I'll meet you on the roof
of the high school gym.

01:23:13.864 --> 01:23:15.324
On the roof. 10-4.

01:23:15.407 --> 01:23:18.368
- Hey, it's him!
- Hey, he's in disguise.

01:23:18.452 --> 01:23:20.329
Guys, what's that?

01:23:22.164 --> 01:23:23.874
Come on! Let's get him!

01:23:31.131 --> 01:23:32.257
Damn!

01:23:41.725 --> 01:23:43.352
♪ MARVIN: (SINGING) <i>Earth angel ♪</i>

01:23:43.560 --> 01:23:46.313
<i>♪ Please be mine ♪</i>

01:23:46.980 --> 01:23:49.107
<i>♪ My darling dear ♪</i>

01:23:49.274 --> 01:23:52.486
<i>♪ Love you for all time ♪</i>

01:23:53.111 --> 01:23:55.864
<i>♪ I'm just a fool ♪</i>

01:23:57.699 --> 01:24:00.619
<i>♪ A fool in love ♪</i>

01:24:02.120 --> 01:24:05.374
<i>♪ with you ♪</i>

01:24:10.087 --> 01:24:11.380
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

01:24:11.463 --> 01:24:13.507
All right! Let's do another one.

01:24:13.799 --> 01:24:16.093
Where did he go? He just came in here!

01:24:17.553 --> 01:24:18.720
MARTY: <i>Something that really cooks.</i>

01:24:18.804 --> 01:24:19.805
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:24:19.888 --> 01:24:21.348
Look! How did he get up on stage?

01:24:21.431 --> 01:24:23.725
I don't know, but when he gets down,
we're gonna nail him.

01:24:23.809 --> 01:24:26.228
How the hell did
he change his clothes so fast?

01:24:26.311 --> 01:24:28.772
MARTY: <i>All right, it's an oldie
where I come from.</i>

01:24:28.855 --> 01:24:31.024
<i>All right, guys, listen,
this is a blues riff in B.</i>

01:24:31.108 --> 01:24:34.403
<i>Watch me for the changes,
and try and keep up, okay?</i>

01:24:34.486 --> 01:24:36.780
(ROCK 'N' ROLL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:24:39.866 --> 01:24:42.452
- Doc. Doc, come in!
- Marty, come in.

01:24:42.536 --> 01:24:47.082
Listen, Biff's guys chased me into the gym,
and they're going to jump me.

01:24:47.165 --> 01:24:48.584
Then get out of there!

01:24:48.667 --> 01:24:53.005
No, Doc, not me. The other me. The one
that's up on stage playing <i>Johnny B. Goode.</i>

01:24:53.088 --> 01:24:55.882
Great Scott! Your other self will miss
the lightning bolt at the clock tower,

01:24:55.966 --> 01:24:58.010
you won't get back to the future,
and we'll have a major paradox!

01:24:58.093 --> 01:25:00.012
Wait, wait, wait. A paradox?

01:25:00.095 --> 01:25:02.431
You mean one of those things
that can destroy the universe?

01:25:02.514 --> 01:25:04.808
Precisely. Marty, you have to stop
those guys at all costs,

01:25:04.891 --> 01:25:07.853
but without being seen by your other self
or your parents.

01:25:07.978 --> 01:25:09.187
10-4.

01:25:10.522 --> 01:25:11.857
What the hell?

01:25:15.569 --> 01:25:17.070
- Where is he?
- Who?

01:25:17.154 --> 01:25:18.697
- Calvin Klein.
- Who?

01:25:18.780 --> 01:25:22.200
- The guy with the hat, where is he?
- Oh. He went that way.

01:25:22.284 --> 01:25:26.038
I think he took your wallet.
I think he took his wallet.

01:25:26.788 --> 01:25:28.707
<i>♪ Go, Johnny, go, go, go ♪</i>

01:25:30.459 --> 01:25:32.044
<i>♪ Johnny B. Goode ♪</i>

01:25:50.562 --> 01:25:51.897
<i>♪ Go, go ♪</i>

01:25:52.314 --> 01:25:54.274
<i>♪ Go, Johnny, go, go ♪</i>

01:25:55.108 --> 01:25:57.110
<i>♪ Go, Johnny, go, go, go ♪</i>

01:25:57.986 --> 01:26:00.072
<i>♪ Go, Johnny, go, go ♪</i>

01:26:00.906 --> 01:26:02.908
<i>♪ Go, Johnny, go, go, go ♪</i>

01:26:04.451 --> 01:26:05.911
<i>♪ Johnny B. Goode ♪</i>

01:26:51.790 --> 01:26:54.459
(HEAVY METAL RIFFS PLAYING)

01:27:00.132 --> 01:27:01.842
(FEEDBACK)

01:27:05.137 --> 01:27:07.597
(HIGH-PITCH NOTE PLAYING)

01:27:08.765 --> 01:27:10.475
(AMPLIFIERS HUMMING)

01:27:11.727 --> 01:27:12.978
(SIGHS)

01:27:22.404 --> 01:27:25.115
<i>I guess you guys aren't ready for that yet.</i>

01:27:26.158 --> 01:27:28.744
<i>But your kids are going to love it.</i>

01:27:37.169 --> 01:27:39.546
Hey, Doc, success. Everything's cool.

01:27:39.629 --> 01:27:42.799
DOC: <i>Great. I'll be landing at the school roof
in about one minute.</i>

01:27:42.883 --> 01:27:44.509
I'll be there.

01:27:52.058 --> 01:27:53.268
Lorraine.

01:27:53.351 --> 01:27:56.772
Marty, that was very interesting music.

01:28:01.067 --> 01:28:04.196
I hope you don't mind, but George
asked if he could take me home.

01:28:04.529 --> 01:28:07.574
Great.
Lorraine, I had a feeling about you two.

01:28:07.657 --> 01:28:09.493
I have a feeling, too.

01:28:10.076 --> 01:28:11.703
Hey, butthead!

01:28:12.662 --> 01:28:15.582
You think that stupid disguise
would get by me?

01:28:16.374 --> 01:28:20.378
Let's have it out. You and me, right now.

01:28:21.463 --> 01:28:22.881
No, thanks.

01:28:24.716 --> 01:28:26.843
What's the matter?

01:28:26.927 --> 01:28:28.929
Where are you going?

01:28:29.012 --> 01:28:30.722
Are you chicken?

01:28:31.973 --> 01:28:35.185
That's it, isn't it?
Nothing but a little chicken.

01:28:49.825 --> 01:28:53.495
Nobody calls me chicken.

01:29:01.753 --> 01:29:03.213
What the hell?

01:29:05.340 --> 01:29:07.175
You steal my stuff?

01:29:07.592 --> 01:29:08.885
(GROANING)

01:29:08.969 --> 01:29:11.054
And this one's for my car!

01:29:26.653 --> 01:29:28.071
(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:29:36.705 --> 01:29:37.831
- (THUNDER RUMBLING)
- Doc!

01:29:38.039 --> 01:29:40.083
Doc! I blew it.

01:29:40.750 --> 01:29:44.254
Biff nailed me. He took the book.
He drove away with it in his car.

01:29:44.337 --> 01:29:46.464
It's my fault, Doc.
I should have got out of there sooner.

01:29:46.548 --> 01:29:48.383
No time for that now. Which way did he go?

01:29:48.466 --> 01:29:50.677
- East towards the River Road Tunnel.
- Get in!

01:30:02.022 --> 01:30:03.607
Yes!

01:30:03.690 --> 01:30:05.150
There he is, Doc!

01:30:05.567 --> 01:30:09.529
- Let's land on him. We'll cripple his car.
- Marty, he's in a '46 Ford. We're a DeLorean.

01:30:09.613 --> 01:30:12.157
He'd rip through us like we were tin foil.

01:30:12.240 --> 01:30:14.242
- So what do we do?
- I have a plan.

01:30:14.326 --> 01:30:16.411
MAN ON RADIO:
<i>Repeating tonight's earlier weather bulletin,</i>

01:30:16.494 --> 01:30:18.997
<i>a severe thunderstorm is heading
for Hill Valley.</i>

01:30:41.478 --> 01:30:43.563
<i>Serving Hill Valley and all of Hill County,</i>

01:30:43.647 --> 01:30:46.733
<i>you're tuned to KKHV,
